---
import { studioName } from "@zoggy/branding";
import StudioLayout from "../../layouts/StudioLayout.astro";

const title = `Groundmaker | ${studioName}`;
const description = `A world-authoring toolchain for creating terrain, zones, and server-compatible world data for the MMO.`;
---
<StudioLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="gm-hero" aria-labelledby="gm-title">
    <div class="gm-hero-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">In development</p>
      <h1 id="gm-title">Groundmaker<br /><span style="color:#6ee7b7">&amp; World Pipeline</span></h1>
      <p class="gm-lead">Terrain and zone-authoring tools that create neutral world data readable by both the Godot client and the authoritative Go server.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section" aria-label="Pipeline">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="pipeline-flow">
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">01</span>
          <h3>Terrain</h3>
          <p>Height maps and elevation data</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">02</span>
          <h3>Environment</h3>
          <p>Object placement and collision</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">03</span>
          <h3>Export</h3>
          <p>Neutral zone data format</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pipeline-step">
          <span class="step-num">04</span>
          <h3>Consume</h3>
          <p>Client renders, server validates</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section" aria-label="Details">
    <div class="section-inner wide-grid">
      <article class="card text-stack">
        <h2>Purpose</h2>
        <p>Groundmaker creates terrain and neutral server-readable zone data. Terrain3D handles broad client visuals. The Go server consumes exported gameplay information rather than Godot-specific terrain resources.</p>
        <p>This separation means the server can validate movement, spawning, and zone logic independently of the client rendering pipeline.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card text-stack">
        <h2>Pipeline stages</h2>
        <ul class="note-list">
          <li>Terrain height and elevation maps</li>
          <li>Environment and object placement</li>
          <li>Walkability and collision data</li>
          <li>Zone boundary definitions</li>
          <li>Server-unit coordinate translation</li>
          <li>Neutral export format for both client and server</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section" aria-label="Technical challenge">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="section-heading" style="max-width: 100%; text-align: center">
        <h2>Keeping a Godot World and Go Server on the Same Grid</h2>
        <p style="max-width: 48rem; margin: 0 auto">The world pipeline translates between server units, Godot units, logical tiles, elevation layers, entity origins, collision footprints, and area-of-interest cells. Getting these measurements consistent across two very different runtimes is the core engineering challenge.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</StudioLayout>
<style>
  .gm-hero {
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 22% 18%, rgba(52,211,153,0.28), transparent 22rem), radial-gradient(circle at 78% 22%, rgba(56,189,248,0.2), transparent 20rem), linear-gradient(155deg, #064e3b 0%, #0f172a 62%, #020617 100%);
    color: #f8fafc;
    min-height: min(520px, 60svh);
    display: grid;
    align-items: center;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 9vw, 6rem) var(--space-page);
  }
  .gm-hero-inner { width: min(100%, 72rem); margin: 0 auto; }
  .gm-hero .eyebrow { color: #6ee7b7; }
  .gm-hero h1 { color: #f8fafc; }
  .gm-lead { max-width: 42rem; margin: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem) 0 0; font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.6rem); line-height: 1.3; color: #a7f3d0; }
  .pipeline-flow { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 12rem), 1fr)); gap: 1.25rem; }
  .pipeline-step { border-radius: var(--radius-card); padding: clamp(1.2rem, 3vw, 1.6rem); border: 1px solid rgba(17,24,39,0.12); background: rgba(255,255,255,0.62); text-align: center; }
  .pipeline-step h3 { margin: 0.5rem 0 0.35rem; font-family: var(--font-display); font-weight: 900; }
  .pipeline-step p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #374151; }
  .step-num { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 2.5rem; height: 2.5rem; border-radius: 50%; background: #111827; color: #6ee7b7; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 900; }
</style>
